{
  "stem": "12053.4",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "But a lot of the other Jews looked-- I think in a way, I think it must have faded by now because there's so much intermarriage now between them and our children and that.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "So that doesn't count anymore.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "But in those days, it did count, and we really felt it.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "But I was too happy to feel anything like that.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "I had my parents.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "After what?",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "After Birmingham?",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Well, I'm going to make a very big jump.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I-- I married in Birmingham.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I raised my--",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I married Hanukkah time 1945, end of the year.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And that was wonderful.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And next year, I had my first child.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "In the groups that I started to go to in Birmingham.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "You know, there were some-- they were mixed already, some refugees, some English Jews background.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But it was the-- what was it called?",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "[HEBREW].",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "That's like the Orthodox-- a bit more Orthodox than [HEBREW].",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And there were various groups in Germany.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "There was the-- the lefties, like the Communistic group, more like the-- today.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Then they all went to Israel and started to build a kibbutz.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And because we were Orthodox, my parents wanted me to join the Orthodox group, which I did.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And I became great friends with my husband's family's cousins.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And another friend of mine told me also-- told me only recently-- that she lived in Birmingham.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "I got to know her later.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "She also felt that they were being looked down upon by the Jews of Birmingham who'd been in there for a generation or two longer.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "So it's always-- everybody wants to have somebody to, you know, make [INAUDIBLE] over and look down on.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "I suppose it is the natural course of events.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And I hope we'll never do that.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh, everybody-- we had a radio then.",
      "word_count": 7
    }
  ],
